summary:
Key Material Information:

  • Gas Supply Agreement:
  • 7-year deal with Greymouth Gas NZ (GGNZ Ltd) for up to 7PJ/year, effective 1 October 2025.

  • Option to extend for 3 additional years (from October 2032).

  • Strategic Impact:

  • Diversifies gas supply, reduces single-field reliance.
  • Supports 200–300GWh/year of gas peaking generation (Stratford), enabling 98% renewable generation (normal hydrology).

  • Aligns with net-zero generation by 2035 target.

  • Capital/Investment Context:

  • $2B+ committed to renewable projects (past 4 years).

No trading or capital-raising actions announced.

Summary of Material Information:

  • Director's Share Purchase:
  • Director: Hartley Atkinson
  • Transaction: On-market purchase of 200,000 ordinary shares in AFT Pharmaceuticals at an average price of $2.83/share (total ~$566,000 NZD).
  • Dates of Purchase: June 30, July 1, and July 2, 2025.
  • Total Holdings Post-Transaction:
    • Atkinson Family Trust: 72,259,496 shares (previously 72,059,496).
    • Personal Holdings: 867,826 shares (jointly held as beneficial owner).
  • No Closed Period Trading: No breach of trading restrictions.

No other material capital markets or trading impacts identified.

Material Information Summary

Operational Traffic Report (May 2025):

  • Group Capacity: Down 2.7% YoY (Long Haul -2.2%, Domestic -5.5%, Short Haul Int'l -2.2%) due to global engine maintenance delays.
  • Load Factor: Improved 2.5 pts YoY to 82.0% (Group), 83.5% YTD.
  • Revenue Metrics:
  • Group YTD RASK: +2.0% (underlying, ex-FX).
  • Long Haul RASK: +2.8% YTD.
  • Asia Routes: Passengers +8.0% YTD, RPK +6.1% YTD.
  • Americas Routes: Passengers -8.7% YTD, RPK -9.9% YTD.

Strategic Updates (Media Releases):

  1. Capacity Expansion (Tasman/Pacific):
  2. 1.7M seats added for Oct 2025–Mar 2026 (+130K on Tasman routes, +25K to Pacific Islands).
  3. 8% increase in premium seats; 42 widebody flights/week to Australia.
  4. China Partnership:
  5. NZD $700K+ marketing investment with Air China/Tourism NZ to boost Chinese tourism.
  6. Shanghai–Auckland premium seats: +33% from Oct 2025.
  7. Long-Haul Premium Growth:
  8. North America: 34K+ extra seats (+15% premium seats on USA/Canada routes).
  9. Asia: 11,800 seats added to Taipei (+27%), 49% premium seat boost to Bali.
  10. Domestic/Fleet Updates:
  11. 36K seats added on NZ domestic routes (Jun–Oct 2025).
  12. 2 new A321neo aircraft (70K annual seats added; first entered service June 2025).

No material capital markets activity identified (e.g., capital raising, M&A). Focus on operational trends and capacity adjustments.

• Updated FY25 uNPAT guidance: Expects to be at lower end of analyst range ($27.0M–$34.4M).
  • Key drivers: Near-term pressure from global RV sales challenges and softer USA market; manufacturing earnings decline due to reduced volumes.
  • FY26 outlook: Opening net debt ~$500M (ex-IFRS 16); forward rental revenue up double-digits in all markets except USA (single-digit decline there).
  • Impairment risk: Preliminary assessment indicates potential goodwill impairment (NZ$36M for USA business); other non-cash one-offs may impact statutory NPAT (no covenant impact).
  • Forward bookings: NZ/AU rentals +25% YoY; USA bookings initially dropped 40–50% post-Liberation Day but partially recovered.

(Excludes operational initiatives deemed non-material pending further details.)
